sentences: Michael Hornburg (born October 31, 1960) is an American writer and literary agent.
He has published two novels: Bongwater (1995) and Downers Grove (1999), both of which have been adapted into feature films.
He has published two novels: Bongwater (1995) and Downers Grove (1999), both of which have been adapted into feature films.
He attended Downers Grove South High School, where he graduated in 1978.
His first novel, Bongwater, published in 1995, was based on his experiences living there, as well as his purported relationship with a then-unknown Courtney Love.
In 1998, Bongwater was adapted into a film of the same name starring Luke Wilson, Alicia Witt, Brittany Murphy, and Jack Black.
His second book, a coming-of-age horror novel titled Downers Grove, was published in 1999, and reprinted in 2001.
